Update Log

1. Fixed DATABASE_URL fallback
- Problem: Server crashed when .env had an empty DATABASE_URL value.
- Cause: db/models.py passed an empty string directly to SQLAlchemy.
- Fix: Changed DATABASE_URL loading to use SQLite when the env value is empty.
- File: db/models.py

2. Preserved scan progress across tab changes
- Problem: Running scan state was reset when moving from scan to stats/findings/patches.
- Cause: AnalyzeView was unmounted on every tab change, clearing local state and polling interval.
- Fix: Kept AnalyzeView mounted and only hid it with display:none when another tab is active.
- File: dashboard/src/App.jsx

Verification
- Confirmed DB initialization uses SQLite correctly.
- Ran dashboard production build successfully with npm run build.
